quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  6,143,"ňĻGod has createdňļ four pairs: a pair of sheep and a pair of goats‚ÄĒask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúHas He forbidden ňĻto youňļ the two males or the two females or what is in the wombs of the two females? Tell me with knowledge, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒ"
  6,144,"and a pair of camels and a pair of oxen. Ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúHas He forbidden ňĻto youňļ the two males or the two females or what is in the wombs of the two females? Or were you present when God gave you this commandment?‚ÄĚ Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against God to mislead others without ňĻanyňļ knowledge? Surely God does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  6,145,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI do not find in what has been revealed to me anything forbidden to eat except carrion, running blood, swine‚ÄĒwhich is impure‚ÄĒor a sinful offering in the name of any other than God. But if someone is compelled by necessity‚ÄĒneither driven by desire nor exceeding immediate need‚ÄĒthen surely your Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  6,146,"For those who are Jewish, We forbade every animal with undivided hoofs and the fat of oxen and sheep except what is joined to their backs or intestines or mixed with bone. In this way We rewarded them for their violations. And We are certainly truthful"
